CO2 can be converted to fuels with renewable, solar-derived hydrogen and solar heat, as discussed above. For example, the reverse-water–gas shift reaction (RWGS):CO2+H2→CO + H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
